A non-zero total bill amount implies that the customer has had some form of financial activity in the past six months; 
payment frequency can be an indicator of customer loyalty or financial stability; 
a customer's age might influence their payment habits or financial obligations.

- High credit limits are considered to be greater than 10,000; 
- A payment status of -1 indicates a missed payment;
- Outstanding bills refer to bill amounts greater than 0;
- High transaction frequency is defined as more than 5 transactions.

; A 'high-credit' customer refers to someone with a credit limit balance greater than $50,000; 
; A 'stable employee' refers to someone who is currently employed by the same employer; 
; A 'high-risk' customer refers to someone with an average risk score greater than 0.8.
